
Right click at the project level and select add / container orchestrator support.
Select  Select Kubernetes/Helm
If its not installed update visual studio individual components

install the [Kubernetes tools for visual studio](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=ms-kubernetes-tools.vscode-kubernetes-tools)
You can debug code runing on the kubernetes with [bridge to kuberbnetes](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=ms-azuretools.mindaro2022) 

I installed chocolatey from [here](https://chocolatey.org/install)
That gave me the helm cli. From there I went tot he root of my application and ran "helm create myapi" and this generated a whole bunch of files under myapi folder.
